            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve">
                <div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" source="#ityr2006"><p><note>i</note>: Sous Flavius Antigonos, le très-magnifique comte et gouverneur, fut achevée la mosaique aux temps 
                du clarissime Jean, comte et 'père', au mois de Dystros de l'an 629, indiction 12, par le zèle d'Illos, le clarissime scholastique. 
                <note>ii</note>: No translation</p>
           </div>
           <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#cmr"><p><note>i</note>: Under Flavius Antigonos, the most magnificent count and archon, the mosaic was completed, in the time of the 
           splendid John, count and father, in the month Dystros of year 629, 12th indiction, through the efforts of Illos, splendid scholasticus. 
           <note>ii</note>:  . . .] many years! </p>
           </div>
                
         </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>It is the location of this building, balancing that containing <ref type="inscription" n="Factions055">Text 55</ref>, which leads to the assumption that it was allocated to the Green faction. The first text 
                indicated that the decoration of the building was an official undertaking by the city. The second text appears to be an acclamation - perhaps of the city - line 1 - 
                and the Greens? But line 2 is difficult to integrate. <!-- check for reds? --></p>
                
            </div>
            
